data.title: Population density in Asia
data.meta_description: The average for 2021 based on 47 countries was 1016 people per square km. The highest value was in  Macao: 20806 people per square km and the lowest value was in  Mongolia: 2 people per square km. The indicator is available from 1961 to 2021. Below is a chart for all countries where data are available.
